    <thetext>Created attachment 1135758
patch to spec file

Description of problem:
Plugin &quot;replaygain&quot; is actually generated upon build but removed upon install.  A comment in the spec file provides a rationale:

# **** Disabled plugins ****
# due to missing dependencies or dependencies being in rpmfusion
...
# replaygain --&gt; mp3gain (rpmfusion only)

However, mp3gain is not a strict dependency of this plugin but merely a particular backend option.  A functional GStreamer 1.0 backend is also supported, and all of its dependencies are available in official Fedora repositories, so there is no need to disable this plugin.


Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
1.3.17-1.fc24
(see:  http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/buildinfo?buildID=734412)

Additional info:
Attached is a patch to the RPM spec file.  It successfully builds SRPM and RPMs (via mock) in Fedora 23, and I have confirmed that the replaygain feature is functional when configured according to official docs:

http://beets.readthedocs.org/en/v1.3.17/plugins/replaygain.html#gstreamer</thetext>
